A COURT case against four men accused of making racist remarks at a demonstration has been dropped. Crown drops race threat demo case A COURT case against four men accused of making racist remarks at a demonstration has been dropped.It was alleged that Ross McCallum, 37, Gary Biggar, 32, Ryan McCue, 34, and Rory Skene, 31, behaved in a &quot;threatening or abusive manner&quot; on June 16, 2012, at West George Street, Glasgow.Prosecutors decided not to proceed with the Glasgow trial.BNP leader Nick Griffin had attended an earlier hearing. 